IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO INSPIRE YOUNG PEOPLE AND THEIR FAMILIES TO DISCOVER THE MAGIC OF THEATER.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO INSPIRE YOUNG PEOPLE AND THEIR FAMILIES TO DISCOVER THE MAGIC OF THEATER, FIND THEIR VOICES, AND ENRICH THEIR COMMUNITIES. THEATER IS UTILIZED AS A TOOL IN THE EDUCATIONAL AND SOCIAL DEVELOPMENT OF YOUNG PEOPLE TO PROVIDE FORMAL EDUCATION IN THE PERFORMING ARTS.
IRS990.Desc: PRODUCTION - THE THEATER STRIVES TO INTRODUCE YOUNG PEOPLE TO A MIX OF BOTH TRADITIONAL FAVORITES AND GROUND-BREAKING ORIGINAL PRODUCTIONS. PRODUCTIONS ARE SELECTED TO APPEAL TO A WIDE RANGE OF TASTES, AGES, AND ABILITIES. THE 22-23 SEASON INCLUDED 8 MAINSTAGE PRODUCTIONS AS WELL AS 2 PRODUCTIONS TARGETED TOWARDS VERY YOUNG AUDIENCES. PRODUCTION ATTENDANCE FOR ALL 10 SHOWS TOTALED APPROXIMATELY 85,000.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: EDUCATION - THE OMAHA THEATER COMPANY WAS ONE OF THE FIRST IN OMAHA TO OFFER CLASSES IN THE THEATER ARTS, AND TODAY, STANDS AS A LEADING PROGRAM AND TRAINING GROUND FOR YOUNG ARTISTS INTERESTED IN PURSUING A CAREER IN THEATER. THE EDUCATION PROGRAM INCLUDES THREE MAIN AREAS. FIELD TRIPS, TOURS AND WORKSHOPS - ELEMENTARY SCHOOL STUDENTS OF ALL AGES ATTEND SHOWS OR WORKSHOPS OR HAVE TOURING SHOWS AND WORKSHOPS PRESENTED A THEIR SCHOOLS. THE THEATER WORKS WITH OVER 70 AREA SCHOOLS AND SERVES MORE THAN 35,000 STUDENTS EVERY YEAR. DRAMA EDUCATION - DRAMA CLASSES PROMOTE CREATIVITY AND PROVIDE STUDENTS WITH AN ENVIRONMENT TO EXPLORE THEIR TALENT AND IMAGINATION. IN DRAMA CLASSES, YOUNG PEOPLE LEARN HOW TO USE THEIR BODIES TO TELL AS STORY, USE THEIR VOICE, AND HOW TO STRETCH THEIR IMAGINATION. CLASSES INCLUDE ACTING, DIRECTING, PLAYWRITING, IMPROV, STAGECRAFT, PUPPETRY, FILMMAKING, AND MORE. BROADWAY - BROADWAY AT THE ROSE IS A COMPLETE MUSICAL THEATER, VOICE, ACTING AND DANCE TRAINING PROGRAM FOR STUDENTS WHO WANT TO PERFORM. IN BROADWAY CLASSES, YOUNG PEOPLE HONE THEIR SKILLS AND PREPARE TO TAKE THE STAGE AT SCHOOL, IN COMMUNITY PRODUCTIONS, AND EVEN ON THE ROSE MAINSTAGE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: OUTREACH - COMMUNITY CONNECTIONS, THE OMAHA THEATER COMPANY'S OUTREACH PROGRAM, MAKES THEATER ACTIVITIES AVAILABLE TO OMAHA AREA CHILDREN AND FAMILIES WHO HAVE NOT TRADITIONALLY HAD ACCESS TO THE THEATER ARTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE INCOME FROM THE FUND IS TO BE USED TO MAINTAIN AND ENHANCE THE STUDIO PERFORMANCE SPACE KNOWN AS THE HITCHCOCK THEATER.

THE THEATER AND FOUNDATION ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. HOWEVER, THE THEATER DERIVES A PORTION OF ITS REVENUE FROM THE SALE OF PROGRAM ADVERTISING AND RENTALS WHICH ARE TAXABLE SOURCES OF INCOME FOR FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAX PURPOSES EVEN THOUGH THE ORGANIZATION'S OTHER REVENUES ARE TAX-EXEMPT. THE THEATER DID NOT INCUR INCOME TAXES FOR THE YEARS ENDED MAY 31, 2023 AND 2022. ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE MANAGEMENT TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE ORGANIZATIONS AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF THE ORGANIZATIONS HAVE TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. TAX YEARS STILL OPEN TO EXAMINATION INCLUDE 2023, 2022 AND 2021. THE ORGANIZATIONS ARE SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.
